02:12:00,400 --> 02:12:02,720
As I inaugurate the hall, I'd
like to present the decision…

1806
02:12:03,360 --> 02:12:08,200
...that the labour committee
has just presented to me.

1807
02:12:09,200 --> 02:12:14,680
All the labourers wanted to
name the hall after the person…

1808
02:12:15,040 --> 02:12:17,280
…whom they're always proud of.

1809
02:12:17,960 --> 02:12:18,880
That is why,

1810
02:12:19,560 --> 02:12:22,960
everyone has decided
to name the hall…

1811
02:12:23,400 --> 02:12:24,640
Dhaniram Hall.

1812
02:12:35,080 --> 02:12:38,800
I congratulate everyone for
this wonderful decision.

1813
02:12:39,320 --> 02:12:41,920
By immortalising the memory of
the late father of Mr. Madanlal,

1814
02:12:42,200 --> 02:12:46,480
...all of you have proven, the roots
are more important than the fruit.

1815
02:12:47,520 --> 02:12:51,640
I appreciate the father, who
acknowledged his son's calling…

1816
02:12:51,960 --> 02:12:53,800
...and gave him the freedom
to make his own choices.

1817
02:12:54,640 --> 02:12:59,240
Mr. Dhaniram could've had his son
working as an officer or clerk.

1818
02:12:59,560 --> 02:13:02,920
But he let his son
choose the path…

1819
02:13:03,080 --> 02:13:07,720
...which was uneven, thorny and
demanded blood, sweat and tears.

1820
02:13:08,960 --> 02:13:13,800
It was Mr. Dhaniram, who wiped
off the feeling of inferiority,

1821
02:13:14,200 --> 02:13:17,520
...related to jobs that
require physical labour.

1822
02:13:18,640 --> 02:13:19,720
That's because he was sure,

1823
02:13:20,160 --> 02:13:25,240
...that in today's day and age, a
farmer, who toils in his field…

1824
02:13:25,640 --> 02:13:27,240
...or a worker, who
works in a mill...

1825
02:13:27,600 --> 02:13:31,040
...put in as much effort as a clerk
or an officer, with a desk job.

1826
02:13:35,760 --> 02:13:38,880
Finally, I'd like to pray that
each young man in our country…

1827
02:13:39,280 --> 02:13:42,640
…should be blessed with
a father like Dhaniram…

1828
02:13:43,120 --> 02:13:46,760
...so that the country
progresses at a rapid pace.

1829
02:13:59,960 --> 02:14:01,000
Friends,

1830
02:14:04,440 --> 02:14:06,080
I don't know what to say.

1831
02:14:09,160 --> 02:14:09,960
Today,

1832
02:14:11,200 --> 02:14:12,400
when I came in…

1833
02:14:14,480 --> 02:14:15,680
I didn't know…

1834
02:14:17,640 --> 02:14:19,200
...that you'd name the
entertainment hall…

1835
02:14:20,680 --> 02:14:24,320
...after my honourable,
late father.

1836
02:14:28,320 --> 02:14:29,480
I didn't know,

1837
02:14:30,360 --> 02:14:31,480
...this was his portrait.

1838
02:14:35,600 --> 02:14:37,160
I had no idea,

1839
02:14:38,520 --> 02:14:41,680
...you love for me
was so tremendous…

1840
02:14:43,240 --> 02:14:45,200
…and I have no words to express…

1841
02:14:47,520 --> 02:14:48,360
What can…

1842
02:14:50,720 --> 02:14:52,440
a son say about his father.

1843
02:14:55,520 --> 02:14:56,440
He's the father.

1844
02:14:57,840 --> 02:15:01,160
And there's nothing
more that I can say.

1845
02:15:04,880 --> 02:15:07,640
My father worked
hard all his life.

1846
02:15:09,840 --> 02:15:10,920
He worked so hard…

1847
02:15:11,920 --> 02:15:13,320
that it affected his health.

1848
02:15:17,600 --> 02:15:19,160
Whatever I have learnt today,

1849
02:15:21,400 --> 02:15:22,920
is thanks to the teachings...

1850
02:15:23,720 --> 02:15:24,880
…given by him.

1851
02:15:26,760 --> 02:15:27,760
He sacrificed his entire life

1852
02:15:29,040 --> 02:15:30,440
to make sure we led good lives.

1853
02:15:33,240 --> 02:15:34,120
I wish…

1854
02:15:35,240 --> 02:15:36,440
my tired, old father...

1855
02:15:37,600 --> 02:15:38,960
could've witnessed this.

1856
02:15:49,320 --> 02:15:50,920
You have honoured my father.

1857
02:15:52,320 --> 02:15:53,760
I feel honoured.

1858
02:15:55,640 --> 02:15:58,440
I'd like to thank our
honourable chairperson…

1859
02:15:59,840 --> 02:16:01,360
...and all of you.

1860
02:16:10,520 --> 02:16:11,600
Lakhoba…

1861
02:16:11,760 --> 02:16:13,680
What Mr. Narendra said was
exactly opposite of the truth.

1862
02:16:13,920 --> 02:16:15,560
What is it? -We can't say that

1863
02:16:15,600 --> 02:16:17,240
...each son should
have such a father.

1864
02:16:17,520 --> 02:16:20,400
But we can say that each
father should have such a son.

1865
02:16:21,800 --> 02:16:22,960
Come on.

1866
02:16:35,080 --> 02:16:36,320
'Get out of my house!'

1867
02:16:36,760 --> 02:16:39,400
'If you want to continue
doing this, leave the town…'

1868
02:16:39,560 --> 02:16:41,120
'so that no can
your damned face!'

1869
02:16:42,760 --> 02:16:46,880
'I appreciate the father, who
acknowledged his son's calling…'

1870
02:16:47,120 --> 02:16:49,240
'and gave him the freedom
to make his own choices.'

1871
02:16:58,880 --> 02:16:59,800
'Lakhoba…'

1872
02:17:00,120 --> 02:17:02,760
'What Mr. Narendra said was
exactly opposite of the truth.'

1873
02:17:02,840 --> 02:17:04,840
'What is it? -We can't say that

1874
02:17:04,960 --> 02:17:07,200
...each son should
have such a father.'

1875
02:17:07,240 --> 02:17:09,920
'But we can say that each
father should have such a son.'

1876
02:18:30,760 --> 02:18:31,560
Hey!

1877
02:18:35,960 --> 02:18:37,600
Gopal.

1878
02:18:37,760 --> 02:18:39,400
Why are you here at this hour?

1879
02:18:40,200 --> 02:18:42,480
I'm…

1880
02:18:43,560 --> 02:18:45,880
You know, you aren't allowed
to come here at night.

1881
02:18:46,120 --> 02:18:47,600
Go home and get some sleep.

1882
02:18:48,600 --> 02:18:50,440
Okay.

1883
02:19:04,080 --> 02:19:07,920
Your father is at the doctor's
to get your examination report.

1884
02:19:08,240 --> 02:19:09,160
He'll come back later.

1885
02:19:10,080 --> 02:19:13,360
From what the doctor said, it
seems that you'll recover soon.

1886
02:19:13,600 --> 02:19:14,440
Thank you.

1887
02:19:14,720 --> 02:19:16,040
We're indebted to you.

1888
02:19:16,440 --> 02:19:17,640
How can we ever repay that?

1889
02:19:17,680 --> 02:19:20,520
If you say that again, I'll leave.
-Mr. Narendra!

1890
02:19:20,680 --> 02:19:22,840
I'm actually leaving for work.

1891
02:19:23,080 --> 02:19:25,280
If you need something, please
tell the servant. -Sure.

1892
02:19:25,360 --> 02:19:26,320
I'll take your leave.

1893
02:19:27,240 --> 02:19:29,240
Mother, I've been
invited for tea.

1894
02:19:29,840 --> 02:19:32,240
You're always busy.

1895
02:19:33,280 --> 02:19:34,640
When can I have a word with you?

1896
02:19:35,160 --> 02:19:37,960
My dear mother, I'm
never too busy for you.

1897
02:19:38,160 --> 02:19:39,800
What is it? -Go away.

1898
02:19:40,560 --> 02:19:43,600
By God's grace we have everything,
but I feel so lonely.

1899
02:19:43,880 --> 02:19:45,480
The house seems empty.

1900
02:19:45,560 --> 02:19:47,360
The house seems empty. -Yes.

1901
02:19:47,800 --> 02:19:48,680
What do we do about it?

1902
02:19:49,240 --> 02:19:51,240
I'll take you for a pilgrimage.

1903
02:19:51,920 --> 02:19:56,040
I'll feel blessed only when
I see my daughter-in-law.

1904
02:19:56,080 --> 02:19:59,240
Mother, I've told you not to
mention about my marriage.

1905
02:19:59,400 --> 02:20:04,960
But Madan, listen to me. -I
said, I don't want to marry.

1906
02:20:18,840 --> 02:20:20,640
Is Mr. Narendra home?
-No, he's not.

1907
02:20:20,680 --> 02:20:22,000
He'll be back in a bit.

1908
02:20:22,080 --> 02:20:23,960
He has asked you to wait. -Okay.

1909
02:21:04,120 --> 02:21:05,320
It's you!

1910
02:21:08,640 --> 02:21:09,560
Madan!

1911
02:21:10,680 --> 02:21:12,800
Why are you here?

1912
02:21:16,600 --> 02:21:17,800
I see.

1913
02:21:18,760 --> 02:21:21,840
So, the welfare officer was Mr.
Narendra.

1914
02:21:24,800 --> 02:21:28,280
I'm sorry, I couldn't
congratulate you on the wedding.

1915
02:21:29,200 --> 02:21:30,080
How could I?

1916
02:21:30,840 --> 02:21:32,040
I never had the chance.

1917
02:21:33,200 --> 02:21:35,240
Anyway, it's not too late yet.

1918
02:21:36,440 --> 02:21:37,360
Congratulations.

1919
02:21:38,720 --> 02:21:41,480
I wanted to apologise as well.

1920
02:21:42,600 --> 02:21:45,320
I couldn't make it that night.

1921
02:21:46,720 --> 02:21:48,640
Then? -I'm sorry about it.

1922
02:21:49,840 --> 02:21:53,760
You must've left home with
a lot of dreams and hopes.

1923
02:21:54,920 --> 02:21:56,960
You're a woman and you
were out at midnight.

1924
02:21:58,040 --> 02:21:59,120
It was also raining.

1925
02:22:00,440 --> 02:22:06,560
You must've waited for me all
wet and shivering in the rain.

1926
02:22:08,840 --> 02:22:10,320
The clock must've struck one.

1927
02:22:11,120 --> 02:22:11,840
Then two.

1928
02:22:12,600 --> 02:22:13,440
Then three.

1929
02:22:14,080 --> 02:22:14,880
Four.

1930
02:22:16,560 --> 02:22:19,080
Finally, you must've
left while cursing me.

1931
02:22:19,360 --> 02:22:22,800
How can I explain?
-Where's the need?

1932
02:22:23,560 --> 02:22:24,520
You were right.

1933
02:22:25,520 --> 02:22:27,040
What did I have to offer?

1934
02:22:27,800 --> 02:22:28,840
Only love.

1935
02:22:29,400 --> 02:22:31,960
You can't eat it or wear it.

1936
02:22:32,920 --> 02:22:35,480
You're used to good
food and clothing.

1937
02:22:36,480 --> 02:22:38,320
It's all about being used to.

1938
02:22:39,360 --> 02:22:42,480
For example, I can't sleep
on soft and cosy beds.

1939
02:22:42,960 --> 02:22:44,880
Please don't say that. -Shut up!

1940
02:22:45,480 --> 02:22:46,880
I know you're someone
else's wife.

1941
02:22:47,400 --> 02:22:48,520
I have no right to talk to you.

1942
02:22:48,960 --> 02:22:50,440
But, can I not express?

1943
02:22:50,960 --> 02:22:53,280
I've suppressed my
pain for years.

1944
02:22:53,600 --> 02:22:54,800
Can I not tell you about it?

1945
02:22:55,080 --> 02:22:57,520
The wounds have left scars.

1946
02:22:57,880 --> 02:22:59,440
Can I not try healing them?

1947
02:22:59,880 --> 02:23:01,600
I thought, the story was over.

1948
02:23:01,960 --> 02:23:04,280
But I didn't know,
you'd drag it here.

1949
02:23:04,320 --> 02:23:07,080
Madan! -I can't bear
crocodile's tears.

1950
02:23:07,680 --> 02:23:09,960
I don't want you
to fool me again.

1951
02:23:10,400 --> 02:23:11,680
I don't want you to
have fun at my expense.

1952
02:23:12,680 --> 02:23:14,800
I have progressed
tremendously in life,

1953
02:23:15,480 --> 02:23:17,640
...but I couldn't tread
the path of love.

1954
02:23:18,280 --> 02:23:19,320
I lost my feet.

1955
02:23:20,720 --> 02:23:22,920
Mr. Madan, I heard it all.

1956
02:23:23,880 --> 02:23:26,960
Before you accuse this poor
girl for betraying you,

1957
02:23:27,240 --> 02:23:28,240
...did you ever think,

1958
02:23:28,600 --> 02:23:32,200
...her father could've stopped
her, when she was coming to you?

1959
02:23:32,760 --> 02:23:37,360
Did you ever think, she
would've tried to look for you?

1960
02:23:37,800 --> 02:23:38,840
It's a lie.

1961
02:23:39,240 --> 02:23:41,080
If that was true,
she'd wait for me.

1962
02:23:41,360 --> 02:23:42,400
She would've never
married anyone.

1963
02:23:42,480 --> 02:23:44,960
Whose marriage are
you talking about?

1964
02:23:45,200 --> 02:23:46,840
Narendra! -Madan…

1965
02:23:47,400 --> 02:23:50,480
Indu was always yours
and will always be.

1966
02:23:51,400 --> 02:23:52,440
Did you ever think,

1967
02:23:53,080 --> 02:23:55,840
...why Indu never get up even
after seeing you in front of her?

1968
02:23:57,160 --> 02:23:59,400
You said, you lost your
feet on the path of love.

1969
02:23:59,960 --> 02:24:02,240
Did you see, it wasn't you?

1970
02:24:03,960 --> 02:24:05,040
It was actually her.

1971
02:24:05,120 --> 02:24:07,640
She tried to catch up with you,
while in her wedding dress.

1972
02:24:18,800 --> 02:24:21,560
Indu, why didn't you tell me?

1973
02:24:22,200 --> 02:24:24,800
Because, she loves you
more than herself.

1974
02:24:25,360 --> 02:24:29,240
It was her love that forbade her
from being a burden to you.

1975
02:24:29,720 --> 02:24:32,720
It's a coincidence that she
came over for her treatment…

1976
02:24:33,240 --> 02:24:35,920
…and destiny brought the
two of you face to face.

1977
02:24:36,720 --> 02:24:38,960
Probably, she would've gone away

1978
02:24:39,680 --> 02:24:40,960
...and you'd never meet her.

1979
02:24:48,240 --> 02:24:48,920
Indu…

1980
02:24:50,240 --> 02:24:52,040
...why did you think
I'd be so heartless?

1981
02:24:54,160 --> 02:24:55,560
Do flowers make a burden?

1982
02:24:57,360 --> 02:24:58,560
Madan! -Indu!

1983
02:24:58,960 --> 02:25:02,560
I never thought you'd accept me…

1984
02:25:03,120 --> 02:25:04,840
...and give me a
place in your heart.

1985
02:25:05,600 --> 02:25:08,200
I won't ever let you go away.

1986
02:25:11,280 --> 02:25:12,120
Indu…

1987
02:25:13,400 --> 02:25:15,040
I had everything in life,

1988
02:25:16,120 --> 02:25:17,240
...but without you,

1989
02:25:17,800 --> 02:25:19,120
...it all seemed incomplete…

1990
02:25:19,800 --> 02:25:20,880
...so useless.

1991
02:25:25,560 --> 02:25:26,760
Madan! -Indu!

1992
02:25:49,240 --> 02:25:51,160
Silence! Quiet!

1993
02:25:51,760 --> 02:25:53,680
What's the matter?
What is going on?

1994
02:25:53,840 --> 02:25:57,960
Mr. Madan, Gopal tore your
father's portrait. -What?

1995
02:25:59,760 --> 02:26:00,760
Tore the portrait?

1996
02:26:01,800 --> 02:26:03,280
Why? -No idea.

1997
02:26:03,480 --> 02:26:05,360
He was wandering
there last night.

1998
02:26:05,720 --> 02:26:07,760
He was staring at the portrait.

1999
02:26:11,240 --> 02:26:12,200
Gopal,

2000
02:26:13,080 --> 02:26:14,680
...has my father
ever wronged you?

2001
02:26:15,520 --> 02:26:18,040
A workshop is the labourers'
place of worship.

2002
02:26:19,200 --> 02:26:21,440
Having that portrait is like
humiliating the labourers.

2003
02:26:22,120 --> 02:26:24,040
Why do you say that?

2004
02:26:24,200 --> 02:26:25,760
Because, I know Dhaniram.

2005
02:26:26,200 --> 02:26:27,000
What do you know about him?

2006
02:26:27,120 --> 02:26:30,200
He worked as a clerk
all his life.

2007
02:26:30,920 --> 02:26:32,480
He was vain.

2008
02:26:33,400 --> 02:26:36,880
He always thought, white
collar jobs were the best.

2009
02:26:37,640 --> 02:26:39,040
When his son tried
to labour hard...

2010
02:26:39,680 --> 02:26:42,720
...and earn a living
by honest means,

2011
02:26:42,960 --> 02:26:44,760
...he got rid of him.
-What nonsense is that?

2012
02:26:44,800 --> 02:26:46,240
For the sake of his pride…

2013
02:26:46,640 --> 02:26:49,320
…he laundered five thousand rupees
to marry his daughter off. -Gopal!

2014
02:26:49,400 --> 02:26:52,160
He was unfaithful, a thief!
-Stop that nonsense!

2015
02:26:56,000 --> 02:26:58,800
That's my prize.

2016
02:26:59,560 --> 02:27:02,040
I don't deserve what
you gave me yesterday.

2017
02:27:05,040 --> 02:27:05,960
What?

2018
02:27:17,680 --> 02:27:19,160
Father! -Master!

2019
02:27:19,600 --> 02:27:20,400
Father!

2020
02:27:20,640 --> 02:27:21,880
Let go of me!

2021
02:27:21,920 --> 02:27:24,320
Your father's dead. -No, father.

2022
02:27:24,760 --> 02:27:27,040
Where had you been, father?

2023
02:27:27,360 --> 02:27:28,600
Why did you leave us?

2024
02:27:28,880 --> 02:27:29,920
Why did you put
yourself through that?

2025
02:27:30,160 --> 02:27:31,160
Why did you put us through that?

2026
02:27:31,360 --> 02:27:32,680
Don't call me your father.

2027
02:27:33,720 --> 02:27:35,640
I've made some
terrible mistakes.

2028
02:27:36,920 --> 02:27:39,360
Ram Lakhan, take father home.

2029
02:27:39,640 --> 02:27:40,640
I'll get mother.

2030
02:27:40,720 --> 02:27:41,720
Let's go.

2031
02:27:45,840 --> 02:27:48,200
Mother, it's a miracle!

2032
02:27:48,280 --> 02:27:50,280
What happened? -It's
incredibly miraculous!

2033
02:27:50,360 --> 02:27:52,400
What has happened?
-Father is alive!

2034
02:27:53,280 --> 02:27:54,800
Yes, mother. He's is alive!

2035
02:27:55,400 --> 02:27:56,040
Yes!

2036
02:27:56,960 --> 02:27:59,960
What are you saying? -That's right.
Father's alive.

2037
02:28:00,080 --> 02:28:01,160
We're so lucky.

2038
02:28:01,320 --> 02:28:03,400
He was a labourer
in the workshop.

2039
02:28:05,400 --> 02:28:07,840
Where is he? -Come with me.

2040
02:28:10,760 --> 02:28:13,200
I can't walk.

2041
02:28:16,320 --> 02:28:17,760
There he comes.

2042
02:28:26,560 --> 02:28:27,560
You're…

2043
02:28:28,960 --> 02:28:30,800
I've given you a lot of pain.

2044
02:28:32,560 --> 02:28:33,920
Forgive me. -Oh, no!

2045
02:28:35,200 --> 02:28:37,640
Don't say that.

2046
02:28:38,840 --> 02:28:39,720
You're back.

2047
02:28:40,680 --> 02:28:42,120
I feel so blessed.

2048
02:28:43,560 --> 02:28:44,680
So blessed!

2049
02:28:49,640 --> 02:28:51,320
Mr. Dhaniram, we must say…

2050
02:28:51,760 --> 02:28:55,600
...both hard work and love
have won the race of life.

2051
02:28:56,600 --> 02:28:57,880
May God bless you, dear.

2052
02:28:58,160 --> 02:29:00,120
You were meant to be
my daughter-in-law.

2053
02:29:00,160 --> 02:29:01,840
Congratulations to you all.

2054
02:29:02,040 --> 02:29:04,960
The doctor has said, in a week, Indu
will start walking and running.

2055
02:29:05,120 --> 02:29:06,080
What? -That's right.

2056
02:29:08,520 --> 02:29:10,280
But I won't let her run away.

2057
02:29:10,640 --> 02:29:11,560
Right?
